<br>
I did that to Serine after a good month long mess of ebay flames and having to deal with the BS he tossed out, and then finding his character on ebay.   Guy was a huge hypocrite.  Not that that warrants posting of RL info but... you live and learn.<br>
<br>
I don't believe I have posted anyone else's RL information beyond a RL name.<br>
<br>
<br>
Far as Shortman goes, I really have no idea if he was part of some ebay crime ring or whatnot, although he was chewing through 300 items a month back then which was far more than any one person or even two people could run through.  Talking high end things also.  Cloak of flames, sebilite croaking dirk, sibilisian cloaks, heiro cloaks, kunark armors etc etc.   High end stuff back then, and considering a cloak of flames could fetch $8000 (yes, no joke) back pre kunark, extremely profitable.<br>
<br>
The reason I question whether or not he was an outlet for some of the others was merely because many of the others had their own ebay names and their own auctions.  The upper echelon of EV (mostly E) had a good percentage who did actively Ebay or at least dabbled in it from time to time.  The only one I know of that Ebayed considerably and still plays, is Dredd.  But who the heck knows who plays that guy anymore.<br>
<br>
And of course I kept up on it all.  Back before Kunark when I was still doing this, I kept tabs on competition much like anyone would with a business.   That is all it was, and I took the time to know each and every one of my competitors if possible.  It was easy enough to ask a customer &quot;hey I see you bought from XXXX.... what was their name if you don't mind me asking?&quot;  Shortly before Kunark I stopped and got out of it all, so much that went on in that world after that I really have no idea on beyond helping a few people track down a couple scammers.<br>
<br>
I also know the original purchaser of Shortman, and I'm sure that information is kicking around somewhere although it has slipped from my memory.  It was someone I had spoken with on the phone pre-kunark.  A customer back then in WWC.  Female half elf ranger comes to mind.  Mid to high level.  After that my crystal ball goes a bit fuzzy  : P  This individual may have been the second purchaser of Shortman as well and not the first.  I just remember them sending me a tell from Shortman one day and telling me about their &quot;new cleric.&quot;  It was highly amusing.<br>
<br>
Anyways, again, I never posted Crush's RL info. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg>TheTribunal.org</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org/">Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <!-- .. -->
